      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Taking clarithromycin and simvastatin together can significantly increase the risk of serious muscle damage and liver injury, so they are generally not recommended to be taken at the same time without a doctor's specific instruction. It is widely advised to avoid this combination unless your physician explicitly guidelines directed otherwise, as clarithromycin forcefully inhibits the enzymes that metabolize simvastatin. You should contact your healthcare provider immediately to discuss adjusting your cholesterol medication or antibiotic to a safer alternative.",
