      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "No, staggering the medications by taking them hours apart will not make this interaction safe. Clarithromycin still strongly inhibits the enzymes needed to break down simvastatin, regardless of the time difference between doses, leaving you at high risk for muscle breakdown even without feeling symptoms immediately. Given your busy schedule and the risk involved, the safest course of action is to skip simvastatin entirely today until your doctor can review your prescriptions on Monday. Extending this risky exposure could lead to life-altering kidney or muscle problems, so delaying your cholesterol meds until Monday is the responsible choice despite the sinus infection.",
